Archey's frog
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a critically endangered, small, nocturnal, forest-dwelling, indigenous frog, <i>Leiopelma archeyi</i>, named after Sir Gilbert Archey, onetime Director of the Auckland Museum.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: New Zealand native frogs are ancient and primitive. They are small, nocturnal, do not have a tadpole stage, have no external eardrums, have round eyes and do not croak.
