Quote: May 2010 Auckland Zoo experts warn that mining in the Coromandel could push the world's most endangered species of frog, Archey's frog, to extinction.  The archaic frog is endemic to the Coromandel and one other site in the King Country.  The London Zoo also condemns the Government's mining proposals.
